<script lang="ts">
  const html: string = "<h1>Tel Link</h1>\n\n<p>A phone number view displays a phone number as a clickable <code>tel:</code> link, allowing users on mobile devices to initiate a phone call directly by tapping or clicking the number. This is part of the Input/View pattern where TelLink is the read-only display counterpart.</p>\n\n<p>The component is useful for contact pages, business listings, user profiles, customer support sections, and any context where a phone number should be displayed as an actionable link rather than plain text.</p>\n\n<h2>Implementation Notes</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Renders an <code>&lt;a&gt;</code> element with an <code>href=\"tel:{phone}\"</code> attribute for native phone dialing.</li>\n<li>The phone number text is displayed as the link content.</li>\n<li>An optional <code>label</code> prop provides an accessible name via <code>aria-label</code> when the phone number alone is not descriptive enough (e.g., \"Call customer support at +1-555-0100\").</li>\n<li>Spreads <code>restProps</code> onto the <code>&lt;a&gt;</code> element for consumer customization.</li>\n<li>No internal state management; this is a purely presentational component.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Props</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li><code>phone</code>: string (required) -- the phone number to display and link to (should include country code, e.g., <code>\"+1-555-0100\"</code>).</li>\n<li><code>label</code>: string (default: <code>undefined</code>) -- optional accessible name applied via <code>aria-label</code> for additional context.</li>\n<li><code>...restProps</code>: unknown -- additional attributes spread onto the <code>&lt;a&gt;</code> element.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Usage</h2>\n\n<p>Phone number on a contact page:</p>\n\n<pre><code class=\"language-html\">&lt;TelLink phone=\"+1-555-0100\" label=\"Call our main office\" /&gt;</code></pre>\n\n<p>Customer support hotline in a footer:</p>\n\n<pre><code class=\"language-html\">&lt;TelLink phone=\"+44-20-7946-0958\" label=\"Call customer support\" /&gt;</code></pre>\n\n<p>Simple phone link in a user profile:</p>\n\n<pre><code class=\"language-html\">&lt;TelLink phone=\"+1-555-0199\" /&gt;</code></pre>\n\n<h2>Keyboard Interactions</h2>\n\n<p>None -- this component uses a native <code>&lt;a&gt;</code> element, which provides built-in keyboard support (Tab to focus, Enter to activate the link).</p>\n\n<h2>ARIA</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li><code>aria-label</code> -- when provided, gives an accessible name that provides more context than the phone number alone (e.g., describing who the number belongs to or its purpose).</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>When to Use</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Use to display a telephone number as a tel: hyperlink.</li>\n<li>Use when users on mobile devices should be able to tap to call.</li>\n<li>Use on contact pages, business listings, user profiles, and customer support sections.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>When Not to Use</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Do not use for entering a phone number -- use TelInput instead.</li>\n<li>Do not use for non-phone links -- use ActionLink instead.</li>\n<li>Do not use when the phone number should be displayed as plain non-interactive text.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Headless</h2>\n\n<p>This headless component renders an <code>&lt;a&gt;</code> element with <code>href=\"tel:{phone}\"</code> and optional <code>aria-label</code> for accessibility. It provides native phone dialing link semantics. The consumer provides all visual styling including typography, color, underline treatment, and icon placement.</p>\n\n<h2>Styles</h2>\n\n<p>The consumer provides all CSS styling. The component renders with a <code>.tel-link</code> class for targeting. No default styles are included — this is a fully headless component.</p>\n\n<h2>Testing</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Verify the component renders a <code>&lt;a&gt;</code> element with class <code>tel-link</code></li>\n<li>Verify aria-label` -- when provided, gives an accessible name that provides more context than the phone number alone (e.g., describing who the number belongs to or its purpose).</li>\n<li>Verify pass-through attributes are applied</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Advice</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Designers</strong>: Style phone links distinctly from other text so users recognize them as actionable. Consider adding a phone icon to reinforce the call-to-action.</li>\n<li><strong>Developers</strong>: Include the country code in the <code>phone</code> prop for reliable international dialing (e.g., \"+1-555-0100\"). Use the <code>label</code> prop to provide context like \"Call customer support at +1-555-0100\".</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Composition</h2>\n\n<p>TelLink and TelInput follow the Input/Link pattern. TelLink provides the read-only clickable <code>tel:</code> link for display, while TelInput provides the editable telephone input for forms. Use them together for view and edit modes of phone number data.</p>\n\n<h2>Related components</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li><code>tel-input</code> — an input for entering a telephone number &lt;input type=\"tel\"&gt;</li>\n<li><code>email-link</code> — a mailto hyperlink for an email address</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>References</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>MDN tel: links: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/a#linking_to_telephone_numbers</li>\n<li>WAI-ARIA Link Role: https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.2/#link</li>\n</ul>";
  // BEGIN auto-generated component example consts
  const demoHtml: string = "<a class=\"tel-link\" href=\"tel:+1234567890\">+1 234 567 890</a>";
  const svelteSource: string = "// In your Svelte component:\nimport TelLink from \"lily-design-system-svelte-headless/components/TelLink/TelLink.svelte\";\n\n<TelLink>TelLink</TelLink>\n";
  // END auto-generated component example consts
</script>

